model_explanation: the prosodic focus on "BILL" means Sam gave grapes only to Bill and no one else. If S2 says Sam also gave Sue grapes, that contradicts S1's meaning.
the prosodic focus on "SUE" means that Sam only gave oranges to Sue and nobody else. S2 directly contradicts this by saying Sam also gave Rob oranges.
the focus is on "SUE", meaning Sam only gave grapes to Sue and no one else. If he didn't give Ellen grapes, that is consistent with S1.
the focus on "TOM" means Sam gave apples only to Tom and no one else. It follows that he didn't give Tom anything else like grapes, so S2 is entailed.
the focus on "ROB" means Sam only gave oranges to Rob and nothing else. S2 contradicts this by saying he also gave Rob apples.
the prosodic focus on "SUE" means that Sam gave grapes exclusively to Sue and nobody else. Therefore, it entails that Sam did not give grapes to Tom, making S2 entailed by S1.
the prosodic focus on "ELLEN" means he only gave bananas to Ellen, so S2 states an event (giving to Mary) that is independent of this fact.
the focus on "ROB" means Sam gave bananas only to Rob. Whether or not he gave Rob oranges is not addressed by S1, making S2 independent.
the focus on "MARY" means Sam only gave bananas to Mary and nothing else. S2 contradicts this by saying he also gave Mary apples.
the focus on "SUE" means Sam only gave oranges to Sue. The question of giving oranges to Rob is independent of that statement.
